102=   I, Rhonda Teagarden, a Court Reporter of the
103=State of California, County of Los Angeles, certify
104=that on this date there came before me at the law
105=offices of Hovan, Wright & McLain, 84 S. Ewing St,
106=15th Floor, Los Angeles, California, on December
107=10, 2007, beginning at or about 8:30 a.m., WALTER
108=EVANS, witness in the above cause, for oral
109=examination, whereupon the following proceedings
110=were had:
111=
112=                  WALTER EVANS,
113=being first duly sworn, was examined and
114=testified as follows:
115=
116=EXAMINATION BY MS. COWENS:
117=    Q  State your name for the record, please.
118=    A  Walter Evans.
119=    Q  What is your home address?
120=    A  Home address is 602 Stanton Avenue.
121=    Q  What's the city?
122=    A  Pasadena.
123=    Q  And the state?
124=    A  California.
125=    Q  And your home phone number?
126=    A  626-555-1515
fmt=pb
127=    Q  What is your business address?
128=    A  12500 Shady Oak Way in Pasadena.
129=    Q  And what is your business telephone?
130=    A  626-555-2020.   
131=    Q  Do you go by Walter?
132=    A  Most of my friends call me Walt.
133=    Q  Do you have any other nicknames?
134=    A  Nope.        
135=    Q  Does Gil Bower call you Walt?
136=    A  Yes, he usually does.
137=    Q  How long have you and Mr. Bower been
138=acquainted?   
139=    A  Lets see, about 10 years I think.  
140=    Q  So you must consider Mr. Bower a 
141=good friend.
142=    A  Sure I consider him a good friend. 
143=    Q  Where did you meet Mr. Bower?     
144=    A  We are both members of the Moose Lodge
145=Lodge and I think we met at a lodge function.
146=    Q  Alright, now where did you attend high      
147=school?
148=    A  Victorville High School in Victorville
149=California.
150=    Q  When did you graduate?
151=    A  1977.
fmt=pb
152=    Q  Where did you go to college?
153=    A  University of Redlands.
154=    Q  What year did you graduate?
155=    A  1982.
156=    Q  What degree did you receive and in what
157= field of study?
158=    A  I received a bachelor of science degree
159= in biology.       
160=    Q  Did you attend graduate school.
161=    A  No.  
162=    Q  Who employed you after college?
163=    A  I got a job with CalEPA the California  
164= Environmental Protection Agency .   
165=    Q  How long did you work there?
166=    A  Until 1987, so about 6 years I guess.
167=    Q  And what was your job title?
168=    A  I started out in the water quality     
169= division as an inspector. But after a year
170= in the water division I got a promotion to 
171= the air quality division as a senior inspector.     
172=    Q  What were your typical duties while in the 
173= air quality division?
174=    A  I visited various regulated facilities in
175= California and collected air samples pursuant to 
176= agency assignments.  I would bring air samples
fmt=pb
177= and my field reports to a third-party laboratory
178= for further analysis.
179=    Q  During the time you were employed at the 
180= agency did you ever collect air samples from the
181= DC Corp facility in Wilmington California?
182=    A  No.
183=    Q  Did you ever collect air samples or inspect
184= in any other way, any DC Corp facility?
185=    A  No I mostly inspected facilities which had to
186= be registered  with CalEPA and regulary inspected 
187= to ensure they were within limits for their type of
188= operation. I don't think DC Corp had to register.
189=    Q  Did you ever collect air samples or otherwise 
190= inspect any facility where Gil Bower was employed?
191=    A  Not to my knowledge.  In the time that I knew
