102=   I, Rhonda Teagarden, a Court Reporter of the
103=State of California, County of Los Angels, certify
104=that on this date there came before me at the law
105=offices of Hovan, Wright & McLain, 84 S. Ewing St,
106=15th Floor, Los Angeles, California, on December
107=11, 2007, beginning at or about 2:30 p.m., SAM A.
108=PARKER, witness in the above cause, for oral
109=examination, whereupon the following proceedings
110=were had:
111=
112=                  CYNTHIA ROTH,
113=being first duly sworn, was examined and
114=testified as follows:
115=
116=EXAMINATION BY MS. COWENS:
117=    Q  State your name for the record, please.
118=    A  Cynthia Roth.
119=    Q  What is your home address?
120=    A  Home address is 4700 Oaktree Place.
121=    Q  What's the city and state?
122=    A  Van Nuys.
123=    Q  And the state?
124=    A  California
125=    Q  Who is your current employer?
126=    A   DC Corporation in Wilmington California.
fmt=pb
127=    Q   And how long have you been employed there?
128=    A   Since September of 2001.
129=    Q   During the period of time you have been
130=employed by DC Corp has the Wilmington facility to
131=your knowledge been ISO certified continuously
132=without interruption?
133=    A   From my time of employment to current, yes.
134=    Q   Now, in April of 2006, did DC Corp encounter a
135=mold problem at its Wilmington facility?
136=        MR. MCAVOY: I'll object to form.  He can
137=answer.
138=        THE WITNESS: I wouldn't say - I don't
139=understand your true definition of a "problem."  We
140=know we had identified a mold in our facility which
141=required us to investigate.
142=        MS. COWENS: Okay.
143=BY MS. COWENS:
144=    Q   Now, this mold that was identified at
145=DC Corp's facility, what was the name of that mold?
146=    A   Chrysonilia.
147=    Q   And when was Chrysonilia discovered at
148=DC Corp's Wilmington facility?
149=    A   I know it was in April.  Right now I can't
150=recall the exact date in April, but I am pretty sure
fmt=pb
151=it was near the beginning of April.
152=    Q   How many meetings did you attend with regard
153=to Chrysonilia at DC Corp's Wilmington facility?
154=    A   Probably between five and ten meetings.
155=    Q   Do you recall the first meeting that you
156=attended in connection with the discovery of
157=Chrysonilia in DC Corp's Wilmington facility?
158=    A  Yes.
159=    Q   And who was present at that first meeting
160=in April of 2006 in connection with the discovery of
161=Chrysonilia at DC Corp's Wilmington facility?
162=    A   I would say all the management staff.
163=    Q   Who specifically?
164=    A   That would be Sam Parker, Ethan Hunt,
165=John Cole, Kevin Jameson, Ben Scott and also 
166=there was myself - although I was not  on the
167=management staff at that time - myself, my quality
168=engineers Chad Ballard, the laboratory - one of my
169=microbiologists Helen Alvarez and then I think our
170=compliance specialist attended also.  I know our
171=compliance specialist was there as well.  His name
172=was Ron Green.
173=    Q   Was Gil Bower also present at that first
174=meeting in connection with the discovery of mold at
175=the Wilmington facility.
fmt=pb
176=    A   Yes.  Sorry.
177=    Q   Now, to the best of your recollection, what
178=occurred at that first meeting regarding the
179=presence of Chrysonilia at DC Corp's WIlmington
180=California facility?
181=    A   I know the first thing that was really
182=discussed was we established a problem statement,
183=what the problem was in the facility, and then we
184=went ahead and did what they call a fish diagram to
185=try to identify the root cause of the Chrysonilia.
